TakeAways day 7 SDLC

User story: simplified description of the requirement. It describes the type of user, what they want and why, template.

Requirement: As a <role>, I want <features>so that <reason>

Example: As a user, I should be able to make a reservation on Book it application so that I can reserve any room for my team. 

Acceptance criteria : it refers predefined requirements that must be met in order to mark a user story complete.

Acceptance Criteria examples:=============================
==>Verify that only the team lead can make a reservation
===>Verify user can only make one room reservation.
====>
	
===>	A user story is a natural language description of a feature. It's usually accompanied by acceptance criteria.